  "function_name": "_fit_transform",
  "justification": "This is the _fit_transform method of the FastICA class. It exactly matches the description: (1) Takes X of shape (n_samples, n_features) and a boolean compute_sources flag; (2) Returns None when compute_sources=False or an array of shape (n_samples, n_components) when True; (3) Validates and transposes input data; (4) Selects nonlinearity function (logcosh, exp, cube, or user-supplied callable); (5) Clamps n_components to min(n_samples, n_features); (6) If whitening enabled, centers data by subtracting mean and computes whitening matrix via eigendecomposition (eigh) or SVD; (7) Initializes unmixing weight matrix with random normal if not provided; (8) Delegates to _ica_par (parallel/symmetric decorrelation) or _ica_def (deflation) algorithm; (9) Computes sources if requested; (10) Sets self.components_, self.mixing_ (pseudo-inverse via linalg.pinv), self.mean_, self.whitening_, self._unmixing, and self.n_iter_."
}

